EDUCATION IN FALKLAND
In our village there is one primary school and a special school for boys.The primary school has 136 pupils,6 teachers,1 secretary,2 cooks,2 cleaners.Our school was built in 1966 and took the place of the earlier Victorian building which was burnt down.School begins at 9.00am with an interval of 15 minutes at 10.40am.We have an hour's lunchtime at 12.30pm after which school finishes at 3.15pm.When we reach 12 years of age, we go to Bell Baxter High School in Cupar.
ENTERTAINMENT We are badly off for entertainment for young people in the village.Most people travel to Glenrothes for dancing,cinema,swimming & sport.{
